Description: Automated X-Browser Consistency Testing (Dev Tool)
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Binary Mechanics are the creator of DomRector, an automated x-browser consistency testing platform.  We have also created RedGlass, a selenium based open source project that observes and logs browser events. Binary Mechanics is a team of software developers, testers and product owners focused on making it easier to produce rock solid software. We built DOMReactor to take the pain out of cross-browser testing, and to allow developers and testers to increase test coverage while decreasing the amount of time spent on monotonous tasks. To accomplish this, we developed a learning algorithm which becomes increasingly accurate at spotting differences between browsers. We also developed DOMReactor to be flexible, and we designed an API which can integrate seamlessly into your existing test automation infrastructure. For the less technically oriented, we also have a streamlined user interface which allows you to test your web site across multiple browsers and platforms with the click of a button. We love the web, and we want to make sure it looks good for everyone- regardless of which browser they happen to be using. DOMReactor makes it easy to look good.

Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: At [Slush Pile Reader](www.slushpilereader.com), authors submit their manuscripts, readers read, comment and vote for their favorites. Slush Pile Reader will then publish the most popular manuscripts. As opposed to traditional publishers, the core competence, the selection process, is automated and based on crowdsorcing the readers', i.e. the book buying public's' opinions. The publishing and production elements are outsourced, minimizing costs, time to market and maximizing profit and productivity. Slush Pile Reader is an user driven author and reader community and an international consumer driven publisher who publishes what the readers want — not what an old-school publishing house wants to publish. In traditional publishing seven out of ten manuscripts bomb simply because no market data is collected. Slush Pile Reader will change the face of publishing by collecting never before seen data on actual customers: through their votes and additional information submitted, Slush Pile Reader will be able to predict which books will sell before they are even published. Also, by using the collected data, market activities will be based on facts, not fiction, thus minimizing risk. In extension data collected can be also used for additional and traditional revenue streams. Slush Pile Reader launched in private Beta in October 2009.

Description: Boston Chowda Company has been serving delicious New England-style comfort foods to patrons from down the block and around the world.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Welcome! For over 25 years, Boston Chowda Company has been serving delicious New England-style comfort foods to patrons from down the block and around the world. As a family-run business, they take pride in creating dishes that reflect their traditional heritage and satisfy with home-style goodness.  Their award-winning clam chowder – made with local surf clams, rich cream and hand-cut potatoes – has dedicated fans from coast to coast. Fresh Maine lobster rolls offer a taste of summer all year long. New England-style pot pies are hearty food for the soul. And their wide selection of wraps, sandwiches, salads and soups provide something for everyone.  Their cafés offer a variety of freshly prepared meals to sit and enjoy or take away. Catering is available throughout Boston and the Metro North area.  Whether you’re grabbing a cup of chowder or providing a conference luncheon, Boston Chowda Company’s emphasis on quality ingredients prepared with care means you’ll always have an enjoyable experience. Stop by, order online or give us a call today!
